==English==
===Etymology===
Contraction of [[fundamental]], originating in Indian English.
===Noun===
[[Category:English nouns]]
'''funda''' (''plural'' [[fundas]], [[fundae]], or [[fundaes]])
# basics or fundamentals, considered as a unit
#:''Get your '''funda''' correct before you submit the paper.''
#:'''quotations''':
#:*1992: "In my opinion, the '''funda''' is as follows:" &mdash; [http://groups-beta.google.com/group/misc.invest/msg/0fe47958fa1d469a]
# concept
#:''what is the '''funda''' behind relativity?''
# understanding
#:'''quotations''':
#:*1993: "You did not have the '''funda''' to realize that the statistics is an ass." &mdash; [http://groups-beta.google.com/group/soc.culture.indian/msg/b39dd8393c559598]
#:*1993: "But then, your '''funda''' is weak." &mdash; [http://groups-beta.google.com/group/soc.culture.indian/msg/4596874842587e78]
#(''slang'') awesome, cool
====Usage note====
Whilst [[fundaes]] and [[fundae]] both occur as the plural of '''funda''', [[fundas]] is far more widespread.  The pluralization to [[fundae]] is by analogy to [[formula]]/[[formulae]].  The pluralization to [[fundas]] is by the simple addition of [[-s]].

The word is frequently used in [[w:Quizzing In India | Indian quizzing circles]]. 

